This was the first set of scans we did. I scanned m4 in series between haphazardly sampled blades 3 and 5 (of the 15 gathered). All other scans were done such that blades from m4, m8, m12, m16, and m20 were together on a single scan while other scans covered blades 1-15. Because we processed SD_B_L5 differently we forgot to take shoot width and length measures.
There was no eelgrass present in San Dieguito Lagoon when we went to sample.
